{"author":{"id":"622048132944212c32e1b63ec36e2ca816992dfb4432ea3388f2f08fbab7090f"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1448547033,"nonce":"3rQlaaEyNuEJaJ+Fn+Vo91kzOy0=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxMTkwNTIyNDg=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/418","origin":"github"},"title":"Bug for `package_gnu_awk_4_1_0` on MacOSX","message":"Hello,\n\nWhen I try to install `package_gnu_awk_4_1_0` on my Galaxy instance with ToolShed, I get this output:\n\n```\nUndefined symbols for architecture x86_64:\n  \"_history_list\", referenced from:\n      _do_save in debug.o\n      _serialize in debug.o\nld: symbol(s) not found for architecture x86_64\nclang: error: linker command failed with exit code 1 (use -v to see invocation)\nmake[2]: *** [gawk] Error 1\nmake[1]: *** [all-recursive] Error 1\nmake: *** [all] Error 2\n```\n\nIt seems that is a [known issue](http://permalink.gmane.org/gmane.comp.gnu.gawk.bugs/558) and the solution would be to add `--with-mpfr=/opt/local` option to `./configure`.\n\nI suggest to change the `tool_dependencies.xml` file with:\n\n```\n\u003c?xml version=\"1.0\"?\u003e\n\u003ctool_dependency\u003e\n    \u003cpackage name=\"gnu_awk\" version=\"4.1.0\"\u003e\n        \u003cinstall version=\"1.0\"\u003e\n            \u003cactions_group\u003e\n                \u003cactions architecture=\"x86_64\" os=\"linux\"\u003e\n                    \u003caction type=\"download_by_url\"\u003ehttp://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/gawk/gawk-4.1.0.tar.gz\u003c/action\u003e\n                    \u003caction type=\"autoconf\" /\u003e\n                    \u003caction type=\"set_environment\"\u003e\n                        \u003cenvironment_variable name=\"PATH\" action=\"prepend_to\"\u003e$INSTALL_DIR/bin\u003c/environment_variable\u003e\n                    \u003c/action\u003e\n                \u003c/actions\u003e\n                \u003cactions architecture=\"x86_64\" os=\"darwin\"\u003e\n                    \u003caction type=\"download_by_url\"\u003ehttp://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/gawk/gawk-4.1.0.tar.gz\u003c/action\u003e\n                    \u003caction type=\"shell_command\"\u003e\u003c![CDATA[\n                            ./configure --with-mpfr=/opt/local \u0026\u0026 make \u0026\u0026 make install\n                        ]]\u003e\n                    \u003c/action\u003e\n                    \u003caction type=\"set_environment\"\u003e\n                        \u003cenvironment_variable name=\"PATH\" action=\"prepend_to\"\u003e$INSTALL_DIR/bin\u003c/environment_variable\u003e\n                    \u003c/action\u003e\n                \u003c/actions\u003e\n            \u003c/actions_group\u003e\n        \u003c/install\u003e\n        \u003creadme\u003e\n            Compiling GNU awk requires a C compiler. http://www.gnu.org/software/gawk/\n        \u003c/readme\u003e\n    \u003c/package\u003e\n\u003c/tool_dependency\u003e\n```\n\nHowever, `mpfr` has to be present in `/opt/local`, which is far from perfect. Note that it does not support the use of Homebrew. I guess a variable to configure `mpfr` install dir would be better. Any suggestion?\n\nThanks","files":null}]}